.TH "ice_flash_component" 9 "ice_flash_component" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_flash_component \- Flash a component of the NVM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ice_flash_component
.BI "(struct pldmfw *context "  ","
.BI "struct pldmfw_component *component "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "context" 12
PLDM fw update structure
.IP "component" 12
the component table to program
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Program the flash contents for a given component. First, determine the
module id. Then, erase the secondary bank for this module. Finally, write
the contents of the component to the NVM.

Note this function assumes the caller has acquired the NVM resource.
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success, or a negative error code on failure.
